### Describe the bug
I try to migrate my web API from framework to .NET 5. I have some code to get UUID via PowerShell
```
var script = @"$computerSystemProduct = Get-WmiObject -class Win32_ComputerSystemProduct -namespace root\CIMV2 
                    $computerSystemProduct.UUID";
```
in the framework version, it works fine, but in .NET 5 version, I've got null in the result and an error
The 'Get-WmiObject' command was found in the module 'Microsoft.PowerShell.Management', but the module could not be loaded. For more information, run 'Import-Module Microsoft.PowerShell.Management'.

I use PowerShell from System.Management.Automation In both API
I've tried to change the script to 
```
            var script = @"Import-Module Microsoft.PowerShell.Management
                    $computerSystemProduct = Get-WmiObject -class Win32_ComputerSystemProduct -namespace root\CIMV2 
                    $computerSystemProduct.UUID";
```
but get the same result.

### To Reproduce
 var script = @"$computerSystemProduct = Get-WmiObject -class Win32_ComputerSystemProduct -namespace root\CIMV2 
                    $computerSystemProduct.UUID";
using (PowerShell ps = PowerShell.Create())
            {
                ps.AddScript(script);

                var pipelineObjects = await ps.InvokeAsync().ConfigureAwait(false);

                var result = pipelineObjects.FirstOrDefault()?.BaseObject?.ToString();
                var errors = ps.Streams.Error.ReadAll();
                return result;
            }

### Exceptions (if any)
No exception, an error in ps.Streams.Error.ReadAll()

### Further technical details
- .NET 5
- Wndows 8, x64
- VS 2019
